&lt;p&gt;We also don&apos;t have a transposeView which is very handy some days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13723218" author="dlyubimov" created="Tue, 30 Jul 2013 01:58:38 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;We also don&apos;t have a transposeView which is very handy some days.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;yeah. that thought visited me more than once in past weeks &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact, this is something that happens a lot in optimizing deferred DRM operations in my &quot;other&quot; code base. E.g. like Jake pointed out, computing A&apos;A verbatim is pretty naive. Look at the multiply/transpose operations lineage and figure cancellations and optimizations where &quot;deferred&quot; dataset reference plays role of a view. A multiplication result might be computed as a transpose view, too, in some cases. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but that&apos;s probably more than i can go after at this point for the in-core.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
